-- Aditya Birla, Jaypee Mull Bid for Central India Power Stake, Mint Reports
-- Madelene Pearson
-- 2010-06-21T01:40:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/aditya-birla-jaypee-mull-bid-for-central-india-power-stake-mint-reports.html

          
          
             Aditya Birla Group, Hinduja Group
and Jaypee Group are among companies considering a bid for a
stake in Central India Power Co. Ltd., or CIPCL, controlled by
brothers Pramod and Vinod Mittal, the Mint newspaper said,
citing people familiar with the development.  
 The three businesses have received the offering memorandum
prior to making possible bids, the newspaper said. Central India
Power is building a 1,082 megawatt coal-based power plant in
Maharashtra, the Mint said.  
